summary: This file defines a Vue component for a navigation header with a responsive menu and tab navigation functionality.
functionality: The component provides a navigation header with a hamburger menu for mobile devices and a tab navigation system for desktop. It includes smooth scrolling to sections and a contact button that increments a counter and scrolls to a contact section.
relationships: This component likely interacts with other components that define the sections of the page (e.g., Home, Profile, Experience) to which it navigates.
It may also be related to a store or state management system if the counter or active tab state needs to be shared across the application.

identified_relationships.description: NavigationHeader.vue is likely referenced in index.html to be included in the main application layout.
NavigationHeader.vue may use Tailwind CSS classes defined in tailwind.config.js for styling the navigation header.
NavigationHeader.vue is part of the project that is configured and built using vite.config.js.
